data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Browse a wide variety of home dcor, furniture, and mattresses at your Raleigh, NC Ashley store. Visit our showroom today.
data.text:
I have been a customer of Ashley Furniture for over 14 years and I have never experienced such poor service. The delivery of my furniture went smoothly, however I noticed some dirt marks throughout the furniture. When talking to customer service they wanted to send me a bulk of material so someone could come and re- upholster my brand new couch. That seemed a bit much as it only needed to be cleaned. So I accepted a 15% discount to pay for my own cleaning. Upon further inspection I noticed a small tear at the corner of the loveseat and I called back (same-day) and wanted them to just send out a new loveseat. They refused and they further refused to provide me any information so I could contact someone higher up in corporate. Additionally the attached photos are pictures of how dirty the water was from having the sofa cleaned (same day)So my brand new sofa came with more dirt then I what I had initially seen. It was not the delivery team because the furniture was thoroughly wrapped in plastic and other covering. Ashly Furniture has just lost a loyal customer for refusing to rectify the situation. I spent over $2200 for my new furniture and this is their response. I will never shop with Ashleys Furniture again. UPDATE!! Thank you Ashley Furniture for reaching out and making things right. I appreciate your following up on my review to correct the things that went wrong. My new living room furniture looks amazing.

REVISED: Unfortunately my positive initial experience went on a downward spiral. I can't get an itemized bill despite several messages and phone calls. The furniture was damaged by the delivery company along with my home. They sent a replacement and the furniture was still faulty and they damaged my home again. Delivery company made me accept the furniture and would not let me send it back. NO RETURN POLICY! DO NOT SIGN FOR DELIVERY UNLESS YOU ARE HAPPY WITH THE FURNITURE BECAUSE ASHLEY WILL NOT UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES TAKE IT BACK. Just a warning to save the next person Ashley's will try to con. Guess they are trying to make up for all their lawsuits. First set of delivery men actually argued with each other in front of my family. I am extremely stressed and stuck with faulty damaged furniture. People don't have time to do multiple exchanges and deal with repair men. The initial order should be right the first time! See attached photos. I will leave my initial review so you can see how happy I was to receive my new items. I will no longer be a returning customer and will be closing my account. INITAL: Leann is absolutely amazing! I worked with her on two visits and she was kind, knowledgeable, and a pleasure to work with. She gave me room to shop, but was close enough to answer questions when needed. I despise being pressured and hounded while shopping so I appreciated her style and felt comfortable while shopping. I also communicated with her via text and she got back to me immediately and answered all my questions. I highly recommend this location and to work with Leann. I didn't catch the others names, but I also had great conversations with other staff there and loved the friendliness all around. I will definitely be a returning customer!

Let me break this review into two parts - purchasing the couch and then everything after that. Purchasing the couch was easy and Lindsay and her manager worked with us and were patient while we tried a variety of couches. After we purchased the couch, it has been 2 months and still don't have a couch that isn't messed up. On February 3 we purchased a reclining couch set. We received the couch on February 10. On February 17 we called Ashley and provided photos that one of the reclining chairs is bent/not level. It took us a week to notice this since we had not used that seat. I asked for a new reclining couch piece and they said that we would have had to call withing 3 days of it being delivered, so now it's under the maintenance warranty we paid for. The same protection plan that if we didn't use in so many years (5 I think), could be a credit towards new furniture in the future. So within one week we already had to use the protection plan that we weren't even sure about purchasing. If we didn't, I guess we'd be totally out of luck. 2/19 and no one has followed up. I check in again and she says they have to send a new part. 3/15 still no part and I ask AGAIN to just replace the one reclining chair because this is supposed to be a new couch. She says again that it is maintenance now because it's past the 3 days. We are also past the 30 days to just return all of it while waiting on a part. Part arrives next day and is all bent and unusable because not packed or secured at all. I call and get another part ordered and they can't pick up this other gigantic part that is sitting in our garage. Second part arrives 3/29. I call for two days to schedule. On third day I text and they say we are scheduled for 5/17. They aren't doing the repair until 5/17 - more than 3 months after purchasing new couch. I would not buy anything from Ashley that could possibly need a repaired item (reclining couches, etc). I have asked for a corporate contact and they say I have it. At this point if we could we would just return the entire couch. We will never buy from Ashley again.

If I could give negative starts- I would! Do not purchase from this store. Not only was our sales person, Ed, completely incompetent so is the store manager. We purchased a bedroom set for an agreed upon price over Black Friday. Not only did Ed take 3 hours to put the paper work together, we were told we would get a receipt via email the day we purchased (11/18) which we never received. Fast forward to our delivery day (12/2) and the chest of drawers is missing from our order. We called and there was no chest on the order at all. We agreed to every piece being included in this sale and they still had yet provided any receipt of purchase with an itemized list or even a receipt of delivery. We call the store and Ed told us he would look into it and call us back, after 2 hours still no call. We called back to be brushed off again and told again he would call us back. I then receive an email with a receipt dated for this day 12/2 (not the day of purchase) which conveniently leaves off the chest in the itemized list, so I respond saying this is not an accurate receipt and we are still waiting for a call. Ed responds with he will pick back up on the issue tomorrow, mind you this is hours before the store closes and we have already paid for the furniture, we are paying customers he has surely made commission on that he is purposely blowing off. The manager has yet to take our call on the issue and Ed has been no help, saying he doesnt remember the chest being part of the deal and I signed on the dotted line so the deal is done. He did not want to deal with us and we had been nothing but kind and just want what we are rightfully owed. Furthermore, if you do some research you can find almost every piece of furniture cheaper online than in the store, so they say youre getting a deal in store but really that is just a blatant lie. One of the many lies we have been told. Dont leave the store without a receipt of items you bought, they will certainly take advantage of you with no remorse or consideration for you as a customer. Dont expect for them to make anything right or care that you even have an issue at all. Steer clear of this store and the employees, especially Ed!!!

In search of a new bed we had done our homework first. Online research, visiting a few stores and inquiring about choices friends had made. It is interesting that we will spend thousands on a mattress but usually only lay on one, in a store, for 5 minutes. Its an uncomfortable place to lay down, no sheets or your own pillow. Weird. Anyway, we decided to finally make a choice and went to Ashleys Furniture. They had quite a comprehensive collection and most importantly; Purple. In dealing with an aging back and sciatica I decided to go with the relief I believe the Purple design technology offers. At the store we were greeted by a very nice lady with the name of Leann. She happened to be a Sleep Specialist! Lee walked us through the different types of the Purple models. Leann made this experience engaging and personal. Adding into our conversation her own life experiences, made for an easy dialogue. Leann was in no way creating any pressure to purchase and gave us plenty of private time to explore. After giving us a quote to take home I said I would come back in a day or so to make a decision. I did go back for another try getting comfortable on the mattress I felt best fit my needs. Leann set up the sale and remote delivery to another state, with ease. We are already enjoying our Purple pillows! I highly recommend checking out Ashleys furniture and to ask for Leann!

EDIT: My furniture order was wrong and I am still dealing with getting this issue resolved. The sofa had the chaise on the wrong side and the full size bed was missing the bunkie board and storage compartment. Tara was pleasant as well as everyone I spoke to including customer service EXCEPT Samantha Vangieson the Senior General Manager. Samantha was very rude and lacked empathy. She was negative and tried to bully me into taking a discounted bunkie board when it should have been included in the original order. I let Samantha know that I was taking plenty of vacation/pto days off to rectify this issue, and shes telling me that I didnt order any of the things Im asking for so I should just pay for it. I told her Tara ordered them in the store and told me I wouldnt need a box spring with my trinnell bed. So yeah I didnt technically order anything because I am not the sales associate that placed the order incorrectly. This is not to get on Tara because mistakes happen, but when those things happen, respect should take place in getting the issue resolved. Not someone talking down on you as if they arent running a business. Several times in the conversation with Samantha I had to ask her was she the General Manager because I couldnt believe how she was speaking to me. At one point I asked her was she yelling because her voice was very elevated along with a nasty tone, unlike everyone else I had spoken to. Had I encountered someone like Samantha I would have NEVER ordered from Ashley furniture. As a Senior General Manager she needs some help with how she gives customer service. Overall this experience has been one that I do not wish on any consumer and I still do not have the issues fully resolved. The disrespect from today has really been too much for me. Tara was awesome! She gave me excellent customer service and was very attentive. I will definitely refer her to people. She made the shopping process wonderful and I enjoy her energy and how welcome I felt. I am very happy with my purchases.

Update: while the buying experience was great, what followed was anything but. My furniture deliveries were nothing short of a fiasco. During the first delivery, the king bed was missing screws so they had to return it. About half of the furniture was delivered here. During the second delivery, received most of what was remaining except there were 2 items that were supposed to be on the delivery but for some reason were not on the truck. Ok, fine. The third delivery was the worst. They attempted to re-deliver my bed. However, there was significant damage to the footboard. They were going to put it all together and then have someone come out to fix it. That type of damage wasnt fixable so I refused delivery. Further, the coffee table had its legs broken off and the warehouse told the drivers to glue them back on and deliver, but they refused. They were literally broken off. The fourth delivery, had everything remaining except for the bed. However, they attempted to re-deliver the coffee table but the item brought was not at all what I ordered. It had to be sent back. Again. Finally on the 5th delivery the bed and coffee table both arrived, correct items and undamaged. By the time my bed was finally delivered and assembled, I discovered that the frame did not come with slats (even though I was sure to ask about them during the purchasing process and was assured theyd throw them in at no cost because my order was so large). Not only were there no slats, this type of bed frame doesnt even have the ability to support slats so I had to separately buy a bunky board to support my mattress. Overall, it took nearly 2 months from the time I placed my order to having my final items delivered, during which time some items had to be delivered 3 times before they were right. The company really needs to reconsider the distribution outsourcing because the experience was horrendous. During this whole process, I had been regularly communicating with Greg N from the retail side, who told me he would try to get my delivery fees (about $600) refunded for all my troubles. I followed up with him a few times and he said hed get back to me but never did. I finally gave up asking because I figured it wasnt happening. Because of all of these problems, Ive downgraded my review from 5 to 2. Greg working with me for as long as he did is the only thing keeping this from being a 1. While the shopping experience was great, everything that followed was terrible. The likelihood of me shopping here again is very low. Original: I had a phenomenal shopping experience at the Glenwood Ave Ashley location yesterday. I had a pretty large order (over 30 items) and they price-matched everything from the website and ended up saving me a ton of money on my order! Shoutout to Greg N, Greg B and manager Joe for making it all happen! You guys are amazing!

Selection is good and service in the store is good. However, that's where it ends. We purchased a bedroom set in December 2021. We understand the material shortage issues and had no issue waiting for the furniture. As of May, we have received everything except the bed. The bed was scheduled to arrive May 24th between 2 and 5 pm. At 7 pm, still no word from Ashley. We checked online and it time was changed, without notice to us, to 7 - 9 pm. At 930 we checked again and the delivery was canceled. Again, no notice. We called the next day and were told it would be 9 more days before they could reschedule the delivery. The truck was within 30 mins of our house but it's going to take more than a week to get back to us. That's absurd. After hours of phone calls, we reached one person that seemed to care. She told us she was able to schedule delivery for the next day (May 26) between 730 and 1030 am. As of 1130, no calls. No truck. We called back and again, we were told 9 days out. This company will lie to you and make every excuse. They claim they can't contact their drivers and can't control when deliveries are made. They act as if the deliveries are coming from a foreign country and speak a different language. The customer service is horrendous. As the largest furniture supplier in the states, they need to get their act together. I won't buy anything else from them. Happy to pay more for real customer service. Update 5/31/22: After speaking to several different people, we had the delivery of the bed scheduled for today. Original window was 1230 - 330. That didn't happen. No call. No notice. Checked online and time was changed to later window. Finally got a call after the first window of time closed saying it would be later. Truck finally arrived around 445. The guys brought the boxes upstairs, tore them open only to learn that the hardware to assemble it wasn't included. They carried everything back to the truck and left. Trash was left all over the house from the front door, all across the first floor l, up the stairs and into the bedroom (paper, Styrofoam, plastic). Another 100% failure by Ashley. It is almost laughable at this point.

Edit: Lots of fake reviews on here. Original: I liked the selections and the prices are fair. The reason I didn't give 5 stars is because of delivery issues. I get that COVID is affecting EVERYONE, but how can you sell a product that is backordered, but not tell people it's actually backordered. You scheduled a "tentative" delivery date. You put a deceiving disclaimer on your paperwork and website that state that you are "currently experiencing manufacturer delays that are causing unusually longer lead times and occasionally unexpected delays." Just say you are back ordered. Don't give people a delivery date unless you can be sure it will be delivered on that date. I got 2 days notice that only 1 of my 2 items would be delivered on time. That was AFTER I had to call Customer Care. The customer service rep i spoke to made it seem like you were doing me a favor by at least giving me one of my items. Honestly, if there wasn't a 10% fee incurred for returns/cancellations, I'd cancel the order now. Probably the last time i order anything from any Ashley store. UPDATE#1: I was contacted by the company. They are attempting to make some things right, but I won't know until after the last piece of furniture is delivered. Item #1 was supposed to be delivered in the morning, but was contacted and told it would be the afternoon. Will update as I know more. UPDATE#2: Delivery guys made it to our house at 6pm. We discovered that the item we received is not the item that we thought we were ordering with the sales person. We ordered both a power recliner and power recliner couch. The item delivered was a manual recliner (invoice didn't have the word "power" in it, but both items look identical. I will be visiting the store today to discuss. Took another star away from the review..

I WILL NEVER EVER CHOOSE ASHLEY AGAIN Update: The experience has gone from bad to worst. Till now there is no date for delivery, no date for the replacement of the defective product, none are updating (neither the store, which is the worst of worst anyways nor Ashley as a corporate). Just simply took the money and are doing nothing. Please be warned and never resort to Ashley. There is no ethics in this place. Original Post: Pretty bad experience thus far. Paid in Nov-2021 and was assured that likely dates for delivery will be between mid feb-2022. But, got only a portion of the order. Also, the dining table set delivered had airline cracks on the table all over and we did not notice it at first, then after a couple of weeks it started to crack all around. Call up customer care and they said they replacement is nowhere near and any reselection that I like is not available, I am asking for a refund for the set and being made to run between pillar and post. Customer is routing the calls to store personal and store personal is routing me back to customer care, been like this three time on a single day. I have wasted 3 hours already on this and still no solution. In-store orders are good if the product you get has no issues, else we are in a soup. Also, store matches your orders with online price but they apply the discount in a very cunning way, all the items that could be delivered early without any issues are priced high and all items that takes time are priced low. So, if you happen to cancel the remaining orders, you would be ending up losing the most. I am not sure what do I do with a dining table that is falling apart with no dates in the vicinity and I had paid for these items long back. Mony is spent, no usable product and no solution in the vicinity. Beaware .... Note: Online orders are hassle free it seems as there is only one channel of communication you need to take care of. Think twice ...

I would rate a zero if i could. I had a scheduled delivery time between 8-11am. At 10:15 I called an Ashley store to confirm my delivery because I had not received any of my stuff yet. They told me they would call me back when they got in touch with the driver.... that NEVER happened and I was left waiting still at 11:30am. I was on and off the phone for hours with different people and corporate finally told me that my stuff was never put on the truck and they skipped my stop. However, I was NEVER notified of this and I was home all morning missing work all for no furniture to be delivered between the time frame agreed upon. If I am going to spend this much money on furniture with this business and you all dont even have the audacity to notify me of my furniture not being on the truck, this is very unprofessional. I was not even given a call to apologize about what was going on or to try and make it a better experience. Nobody had any answers or responses and I was left waiting all day for my furniture. I am VERY unhappy about this experience. I called to try and find out what they were going to do about this and they told me they were going to give me a gift card to Ashley furniture.... LOL LIKE I WANT TO SPEND MORE MONEY HERE??!! they forwarded me to someone and that person hung up on me... WORST experience

This was our second time purchasing from Ashley. I had been looking for some time now for the perfect couch for our family. I wanted something that would last, look good and have enough seats for everyone. I looked online first, saw a great deal and we went straight into the store that day. It was so smooth and easy. The gentleman who helped us, his name is John, from the Glennwood Ave in Raleigh North Carolina location. He was completely amazing to us. Not only did he answer all of our questions he allowed us to move the furniture around a bit to see what looked best for us. We ended up getting an even better deal because he price matched it from the online deal to the store one and we saved a lot of money. Because of the savings we ended up getting the bigger set because we had saved money. I also loved that there was no pressure on us to buy anything, which is something I love so I know that Im making the right choice. We ending up buying my dream couch and I couldnt be more happy about it. We were in and out that fast and still have no regrets with our purchase! Ive fallen more in love with Ashley furniture because of the hospitality and smooth purchasing.

After we made an oral commitment to purchase a dining room set, the salesman (Raj) asked if he could assist two customers before processing our paperwork. We thought this unusual since these customers had just walked in but we agreed reluctantly, thinking it would be for just a few minutes. However, 40 minutes later, our salesman was still assisting these customers so we asked that someone else check us out. We waited 15 more minutes and then left. We returned 40 minutes later and the salesman was still assisting the same customers but he immediately found someone to check us out. (Thanks Hubert.) Because we needed home delivery, the salesman gave us a delivery person to contact. We did but that has led to one cancelled delivery date after another. To make a long story short, I will never make another purchase at Ashleys Furniture even if you were giving furniture away. Update : We got the furniture. We bought the floor model dining setbut found it curious that one of the chairs had pads on its legs. Not surprisingly, that chair would not sit flatly on the floor without wabbling. I am certain that Raj knew about this! Very disappointing! Update 2: The two additional chairs we ordered arrived today. One of the chairs had a small nail in the foot of a leg and scratched our laminate floor before we discovered it. One of the table legs almost fell off. Two of the screw holes for one table leg had been stripped. Rather than call the store (tried that 4 times previously but no one picked up), I made the repair myself. No more floor models and no more Ashley Furniture! Floyd Ogburn Cary, NC

Zero Stars! We purchased a chair from Ashley and was told it was in stock. Waited 2 weeks for Saturday delivery (not bad). 2 days before delivery was called and told 1:15 to 4:15. Ok 3 hours isn't a bad window. Delivery time came and went and I was called at 5 to be told it would be late. I believe I already figured that out. Was then told it would be 5:15-8:15. But looked at the route link they sent and we were 12th and they had just finished 5th. I'm thinking its not going to be 5:15 but whatever. Ok, change plans and stay home the rest of the night. Waited until 9 that night and nothing ever showed up. No call from anyone letting me know what was going on. Got on their customer service chat and was told there was nothing to be done until Tuesday but he would have someone call me first thing on Sunday. I have to say the gentleman there took my wrath in stride. Well Sunday morning passed and by 12:45 and no call (I know I wasn't patient, they had just opened at 12 but still) I called them. I was sent to main customer service, was put on hold (23rd in line) I just had them call me back. Took a little while for someone to call but only to find out that I needed to speak to the store which they transferred me only to. I again found out that they couldn't do anything until the delivery company was open again on Tuesday. but they would try to get something done and would call me back on Monday. I'm sure you can guess by now but again no call. Since then I have spent the last few days with me reaching out to them because no one ever calls me. Finally being told it will be delivered again the next Saturday (which I had to fight for that), but still not being told a time frame. When asked they said it would be a window of time again. I requested first delivery and considering I already wasted one day on it I don't believe that was a big ask. I mean deliveries have to start somewhere right, why not me this time. Nope they wouldn't do it. I was told it was planned by the delivery company and they have no control. Seriously? I'm pretty sure they pay that delivery service (for well their service) and should have a little say in what happens. I was also told several times I should feel lucky that I'm getting it as soon as I am because they have customers that have been waiting for months for stuff they ordered. Not the right thing to say to me after signing for a $750 chair. I guess I should be so lucky to have them take my money. I finally told them to keep their furniture. Then they couldn't give Us (my wife, god love her jumped in at this point for the sake of my sanity and blood pressure) a straight answer on if I would be charged a fee for canceling. After them telling us they would contact us (of course they didn't) I sent an email to our sales person (the only way I could reach that person directly) I was finally told we wouldn't be charged. My thought is If you can't coordinate your deliveries properly or fulfil orders then don't sell the items. Also if you need to call customer service be prepared to wait a long time to talk to someone or get a call back. Yesterday afternoon I was 128th in line on hold. A little trick... select 3 for placing a new order. The line is a lot shorter and they will still help you! Do yourself a favor and go somewhere else.

Sales was fantastic! Everything after that has been a disaster!! 4 months later we still do not have all our furniture. Original purchase date was April 2020. Our delivery date has changed multiple times and 2 of the times they gave us they no showed. One of the deliveries was to be in the afternoon and they showed up around 7pm thankfully I didn't take the day off work assuming they would no show again. Every time they came they didn't deliver all that was told to us. Most of the pieces had small imperfections and they did offer to get them fixed, yet we have not heard anything since then. All the furniture have feet and didn't arrive until we asked for them to be sent. When we got the feet there was no hardware to attach them. We made another call to get that sent. They only sent us 2 kits we need 3. This morning we told that todays delivery has been moved 3 weeks out. Just want this to be over. I will NEVER buy from here again! I will continue to update this review. Update: they told us the last delivery was to be on last Thursday Sept 24th . Guess what they didn't show up again with no phone call! If this doesn't end soon I'm contacting the better business bureau!! Update: the end is near ( I hope) the last pieces should be here by oct 30th. We still haven't heard anything from the furniture repair company  Update: We finally received all the furniture in December. It's now Feb and we still haven't heard from the furniture repair company that Ashley Furniture referred us to. Very disappointed!

I would never buy from Ashley ever again. Ordered a coffee table and end table the first week of August. Was supposed to be delivered and delivery was a no call, no show. This has happened many times since August. Major incompetence by their delivery crew. Me and my fiance called to complain and customer service kept telling us don't worry about it, they will give a credit for the delivery fee. It was free delivery to begin with! Finally on Black Friday they come with the furniture, only for it to be the wrong color! The sales associate back in August ordered the wrong one! I refused to accept the delivery and the driver called their delivery support. I told them I wanted my money back and they told me to call the regular customer care. My fiance called customer care and they said that in order to get a refund they need to re-deliver the furniture and we have to refuse it and we can get our money back then. What sense does that even make? They refused to give us our money back and set a new date for 12/15. Guess what? No call, no show AGAIN! I will be on the phone with my credit card company in the morning and getting a refund that way. I will never ever shop at Ashley or recommend anyone to shop in their stores. Absolute nightmare just to get a coffee table and end table. I can't even imagine if we ordered essential furniture like a bed, or couches. Absolute joke of a company.

*Update* I emailed the response below and never heard back. After just 5 months our recliner no longer reclines and something is broken internally. I no longer have the patience to deal with this company any further. I will never give this business any of my money again. Look for a company that values you as a customer and the products they sell. This company is not it! I have never been so frustrated with a purchase in my entire life. We ordered at the end of June. While we were in the store, I checked out their website and noticed that the pricing online was significantly cheaper than in store. I brought it up to the sales associate, and she said they do price matching online, but I would have to ask to receive it in person. Thank goodness I checked online before we placed our order! We saved $700 just by doing this, which didnt seem very honest for the people trying to sell in store... very shady if you ask me. We were given an estimated delivery date of August 29th. The sales person said many times that there would be no problem getting the furniture there that date, but it was still an estimate. Our move in date comes, only one piece is delivered on time. We waited an additional 5-6 weeks for the couch. Our recliner is really what has been so frustrating. Its now December 12th. We have a scheduled delivery, after 5-6 rescheduled dates. They give us a time frame of 12:30-3:30. They are now behind, and we have to miss our dinner plans that weve had for a month because they will now arrive after 5pm. But if we were to reschedule it would cost us a $75 reschedule fee. What about all of the times that Ashley has rescheduled on us?! In addition, if you miss their phone call when they are rescheduling, and try and call back, youll be 101st in line, even with missing the phone call by only 2 minutes! I tried to cancel my order a month ago because I was tired of waiting for our last item. They begged me to keep the order even though they still couldnt give me a set date it would arrive. They said after its delivered, a manager would call and see how he could help me with my troubles and accommodate something. I asked what that would be, and they said we would have to work it out? This company is so shady and not honest with delivery times. I will never purchase from here again and I wholeheartedly regret getting a credit card with them to save a few extra dollars. Do not buy from here!!! Try and find a company you can trust, because this isnt the one!

t's unfortunate I can't give 0 stars. Our furniture is visually beautiful and our sales person was initially great to work with, which made us incredibly excited to purchase our new living room set. However, be forewarned of the terms and conditions signed when purchasing your new furniture. We had our sleeper sofa for all of two months and attempted to use the sleeper portion for the first time to find it was broken. It was already broken (upon arrival) with minimal use of the couch itself and no prior use of the sleeper portion. After at least 6 calls, they sent out a "master craftsman" to attempt to fix our couch, and he found more extensive damage than we could even see. Our only option was to exchange the couch. After following up numerous times with the store, our exchange order FINALLY went through in July. I called in August to follow up on the delivery date to be told it would be September, to call in September to be told November, to call in November to be told December. We will maybe have a couch that is safe to sit on by December 31st after having purchased the original piece in February. It's anyone's guess at this point as to when it'll arrive and whether or not I'll even receive a call from customer service to tell me it has been delayed again. I also want to highlight that customer service here is horrendous. I have never been faced with ruder people in a customer facing role. If you want furniture you can use upon delivery, avoid Ashley Furniture at all costs.

This company is by far the worst place to get furniture from. I placed an order in the store and was there for almost 4 hours all for my entire order to be a complete mess. The order consisted of a bed room set, living room set, and dinning room set which were all schedule to be delivered on three different dates. With the first delivery for (09/15) I received a phone call stating that I will be getting my dinning set, headboard, footboard, and mattress set. However, The only Thing that I received that day was a mattress. I was told that my order was canceled and that he box springs were never apart of my order. Also, I cant forget to include that they had all of my things listed to be delivered at the incorrect address in a totally different city from where I actually live. I was told on three occasion that was updated and that didnt actually happen until the fourth time I spoke with someone. So because someone within their company canceled my order instead of updating the address I was forced to settle with my items for the first delivery being pushed to October 6. Now the second delivery was scheduled for 09/29. I received a phone call early in the afternoon stating that the guys were running a little late and my time was being pushed from 5pm to 6pm-9pm. I sat at home waiting all to received a phone call at 7:59 pm stating the delivery drivers ran out of hours and they will not be making a delivery to me. The rep informed me that it was then my responsibility to contact their customer care center and get them to reschedule. So this was now the second time that me as the customer had to get the short end of the stick and settle for not getting my furniture because of their companys issues. The customer service when speaking with people is terrible and its seems nobody can actually answer any questions that I have called with. I was told once I called about the delivery my guys running out of hours that the statement didnt make sense but the next available date would be November 3. Which is another month of having no furniture. I would not suggest anyone to go here and purchase anything not even a coffee table. Everyones answer to things is I apologize, we can definitely compensate you and that too is a false statement.

I dont like to do review either good or bad but the experience I had with Ashley made me write this. We bought a sofa from Ashely in June and still havent received it. We were told that we will get it on September 3rd from the store when I called in August. Then they said the person who answered didnt know but it got reschedule for September 29th. I got email with confirmed delivery for 29th between 2 PM to 5 PM. I confirmed in the morning and was told that I will get it between this time and will get a call from delivery driver 30 minutes ago. I waited for delivery as promised and didnt go out for that time. No delivery arrived by 5 PM so I called the number and was told it is running late and will arrive by 6 PM. No delivery arrived by 6:30 PM so I called again and was told that it got rescheduled between 7 PM to 9 PM. I asked the lady are you sure they will deliver it? She said yes it is already on truck and will get it delivered. I got a call at 8:05 PM stating that it will not get delivered and I will have to call Ashley again to schedule the delivery again and she cant help with it. She gave me the number and the office was closed so I cant reschedule it for next day. They took the truck back to warehouse and unload the sofa rather then delivering to my house. Very impressionable service and very disappointed the way they handled the delivery.

DO NOT PURCHASE FROM HERE. We bought a Sealy's mattress and adjustable base in May, 2020. We wanted the Sealy's base, however, the associate in the store told us the Ashley's adjustable base was the exact same as the Seal's base, however, much cheaper so we bought this one. We were also told we could return the mattress we bought within 90 days of purchasing, (we bought a $2500 mattress). When we received the base it was completely different than the one in the store and none of the same functions. The mattress, was absolutely terrible and after 2 weeks we called and they said we had to sleep on it for 60 days to let our back adjust to the new mattress. After the 60 day period, I spent over 80 hours trying to call and get someone to help me no one would because we could no longer return the mattress. I talked to the corporate office, regional manager, store manager, etc. Never got a call back and I ended up going to the store and the store manager ended up helping me out and saying that Ashleys would go ahead and swap this mattress out for one that was of greater value. We got a new mattress delivered Saturday and when we went to look at it there is blood all over it and the bed looks warped and here I am again trying to get this resolved and spend another several hours working on this. I called yesterday and they said they cannot get another mattress delivered until October 8, 3 weeks. They also took our old mattress so we don't have a bed to sleep on. We called Customer service and were promised a call back yesterday and still no call back. Point of this story, the employees Lie, they don't back up what they say, furniture is not worth what you spend. We will never use Ashleys furniture again and I would highly recommend you looking elsewhere when considering furniture. Completely unacceptable and unprofessional.

This company can not get out of its own way, and you will pay the price. We purchased three bedroom sets April 18th 2020. Delivery was scheduled for May 9th. Delivery day came, and the installers did not have the hardware needed for my son's bed. The called and had new hardware ordered. They did not let us know we had the option to send the bed back and have a new one sent out, and that by accepting this one, we could not return it. The new hardware came, and a new install date was scheduled. The next team of installers came and discovered it was the wrong hardware. The installer argued with customer care for 20-30 minutes about the 12 screws needed. The customer care rep told him he was sending a kit with six screws because that is what was shown. I tried to contact our salesman, Nathan Long, to see if he could help. We never heard back from him. He will be your best friend during the purchase, but clearly does not care to retain customers after the he's made his commission. The new kit arrived, and the screws were not even long enough to connect the pieces needed. I called customer care and after being treated rudely, and getting disconnected (with no call back), I called and spoke to a friendly rep who informed me the hardware they sent last time was for my other son's bed. She then said she was ordering every piece of hardware associated with the correct bed, and guaranteed it would have the needed hardware. That kit arrived and it still didn't have the correct screws. So now it is June 25th, 2020, and I'm still staring at a disassembled bed. Customer care had to call the manufacturer to find the screws, and are hoping to hear back that they are available. I'm still being told it cannot be returned because I accepted delivery. I was also offered a whopping $25 price adjustment for the inconvenience with the condition that no other future compensation can be made including returns or exchanges. Each time be hardware was ordered, it took 7-10 days to get it. I was told they could not expedite shipping on the hardware. We had purchased from this store in the past and had planned on buying a living room set in the near future. Now, I will take my business elsewhere.

Ordered a new sofa and chair 2 months ago. Was told after the sale that they would give us a call the next day. Still have not received a call. Called the store to check the status of our order. They said it will be delivered on the 27th of May. I called two weeks ago to check on the status. Was informed it would be the 27th. Called Friday and the lady who picked up put herself on mute and then hung the phone up on me. Called back. They said it will be delivered on the 27th of May. So Sunday we got rid of our sofa to make room for our new sofa on Wednesday. On Monday, the 25th, they called to tell me the order will be pushed to the 6th... Okay, called and asked if the chair that is not on back order could be delivered cause my wife is pregnant and we need something for her to relax in... They said they would call back to confirm. No call back. Called today on the 26th. I was informed that they would never do a "partial" delivery. She said I should just call Monday on the 1st to confirm it will be delivered on the 6th... So the exact same time that I called last week? Just to be told I won't have our furniture for another week and half 3 days later? I feel like they just take your money and hold it hostage. Very poor customer service. If you do buy anything from this store MAKE SURE YOU CAN PICK IT UP THAT DAY!!

PLEASE READ THIS ENTIRE REVIEW! SAVE YOURSELF! I will NEVER and I mean NEVER buy another item from this company. It should have been a red flag to me when the store associate in Raleigh, NC mentioned the bad reviews online and said that, well you know sometimes things happen and you cant please everyone and how customers will make something out of nothing. That said, let me embark you on This horrific journey Ive been on. I came into the store was greeted by 6 different people while looking around all of which were eager to help me. I finally find something I want and they ran my credit and had me approved and out the door so fast! I couldnt believe how fast the transaction was completed and before I left I went to look at some accessories they had on sale and when I was leaving out the sales rep was already running another persons credit! DANG... its a chop shop for furniture. Anywho... furniture ordered on 10/18/19 and delivery was scheduled for 11/24/19. Okay, I wasnt happy about that time frame but I had a couch in the meantime so I was fine with it. My entire purpose in buying the new living room set was because I had family coming in town for Thanksgiving and my current couch wouldnt be enough for everyone. That said, I got a call on 11/22/19 confirming my delivery for 11/24, Im excited. Here 11/24 (yesterday) comes and goes my delivery window was scheduled for 10:30am to 1:30pm but I have no furniture. At 1:45pm I called the store I purchased the furniture from and she told me they were having system issues and couldnt look up anything. She gave me a number to call that kept hanging up on me. I gave them 30 minutes and called back, the SAME manager answered the phone by the name of Missy (who sounded like death sucking on a life savor and needed to be at home) told me she was going to put me on hold and find out something. While Im on hold this heffer accidentally CALLED ME from a different line and I can hear her conversing with other people in the office. The conversation went like this, well I dont know what to tell him and just tell him the delivery truck had an accident and they finally decided to tell me the system is still down. She comes back on the other line and says, yes our systems are still down and Ive sent an email (which I want to know how its down but you can email) but I have no way of actually reaching my delivery driver. By this time Ive realized my blood is boiling so I hang up the phone and call ANOTHER Ashley store (the one on Capital in Raleigh, NC) and explained all of what happened there, she told me that I could look my order up online and track where it was at. We did this together only to realize my order had been cancelled so she explained it could have been several reasons and that she couldnt personally do anything but she recommend I call customer service in the morning. So, here I am with No living room furniture PLUS I had sold my old living room set the evening before because my delivery was confirmed to be on time. Here we are Monday morning and I called customer service. I explain everything to the lady that answers. I also explain I have NO FURNITURE and thanksgiving is Thursday and Ill have family at my house with no where for them to sit. She tells me the earliest she can get it out to me will be Dec 01. WHERE IN THE HELL WILL MY FAMILY SIT DURING THANKSGIVING? Theyre flying in from out of town its not like I can just change the location. This is where it begins to get hilarious. I asked for a supervisor and she tells me Ill have to call back because they have limited staff. I asked, what time do the supervisors come in she tells me 12 noon. Where I come from thats when people take lunch not when they come to work. I digress. Please, Please, please, please please... TAKE YOUR BUSINESS ELSEWHERE. If you dont believe this happens to a lot of people google the warehouse for Ashley in fort mill SC. Their first 10 reviews were all related to BS delivery situations.

Never again. I purchased a table and chairs from here. It was damaged on delivery, but the guys convinced us to accept it, saying the top of the table could be replaced and it would be faster than a replacement table. I immediately called the store, and after an hour-long process, they said I'd hear from the repair company within two weeks. When the repair company called, they only knew about adjusting the chairs, so I had to call the store AGAIN and go through the hour-long process again. When the repair guy came, he took one look and immediately said the whole table had to be replaced. Cue another call to the store. Then I got a call about a week later saying it wouldn't be covered because we didn't report it right away (although we did). Called the store again, left a message for a manager with assurances I would get a call back. After two days I called back and after some confused back and forth, was told it would be covered. Table was delivered a few days later. I asked for my delivery fee back but they wouldn't even discuss it until the table was replaced. By the time it was all done, I was so frustrated with the whole thing that I decided to just spend 5 minutes warning others away rather than spend hours on the phone arguing to get my money back. TL;DR - nice enough furniture for the price, but absolutely abysmal customer service. Never again!

I love the dining room table I purchased from here. It is a five star table! Sturdy, well made, beautiful. My reasoning for 3 stars is the sales process. I realize Ashley Furniture needs to make money, but they were only willing to deliver free if I purchased the "warranty". We declined their firm offer and walked out. We had visited multiple times and our salesperson knew we wanted that table. A few weeks later, we happened to be out during a snowstorm (most people stay inside) and stopped by the store to see the table again and look for a sale. They were having a "drive foot traffic in winter snow sale!". Everything was 30% off! Wow! The manager would not give me a penny off the price but here the table was sitting there for 30% off on a snow day. I purchased the table that same day for 30% off and im so happy with it. Our sales lady who, had our info, failed to call us to share the sale... we happened to walk in on our own. I really disliked playing hardball for the table I wanted. Hopefully the manager has become more willing to negotiate since my visit(s). **Update, they are still not willing to negotiate here. My advice since no one asked? You can get 30% at least and theres definitely still room to negotiate. Do not ever pay full price. Good luck! :) **I also want to say if you are having issues with responsiveness and if the reps and managers are ghosting you, file a complaint with the Better Business Bureau! They do respond to those.

Purchased new living room and bedroom furniture. Delivery date set for a month and half out .They show up and just drop the furniture off in my living room in boxes and proceed to tell me that they dont put it together after i paid a few hundred for delivery and installation . I call customer service and of course they cant give me a explanation on why the delivery driver said that and sent him back hours later to install,, during installation noticed the dresser had huge hole in it ,, they broke bed during the install from there I told them to take all back and bring all new furniture out they say ok and leave the mirror anyway after I told them to take all.. then I get a call the day before the new furniture was to be delivered and they tell me it would be another week before I get the new undamaged furniture delivered,,, I called them about coming to get the mirror they left and we der a date for pick up that day came and went no call, no show ,no pick up.. I will say I got all my money back and went to rooms to go... Ashley furniture is cheap, there customer service is terrible and i would not recommend this furniture to anyone.....

The walking in experience was fine friendly people but the levels of incompetence is crazy. Im not sure if my bedroom set being new made this experience so complicated but their lack of communication is the biggest issue. Im ok with changes if I know about the changes. Its been a month and I still dont have a delivery date. Hubert was the original sales person and he doesnt know how to use a phone unless I threaten to cancel my order. I hadnt heard anything from him for 2 weeks despite calling twice about the delivery date not being set. Never sent me actual sku numbers for the order or pictures of the set I purchased and still hasnt received the pictures till this day. The set was so new its not online. I finally call and They scheduled it for a random day in the middle of the week while Im at work so we schedule a day that works only for me to call today and its still scheduled for the wrong date. Of course the next available date is another 3 weeks from now. They didnt hesitate to run my credit though. I never had these problems with Rooms to Go and if it wasnt for a credit line I basically opened i would just go to a different store altogether. Ill have to settle for a different Ashley store not as convenient to where I live. I know these are first world problems but if im dropping $1,400 and having a large open credit line on my credit i want what I ordered and i shouldnt have to wait almost 2 months to get it. I dont even remember what it looked like and frankly dont want it anymore

Absolutely horrible first time experience with this store. Poor customer service and poor communication all around. Yes, when you go in to purchase the experience is pleasant, but once the money is handled no one follows up. The delivery process is unorganized and the salesperson does not check to make sure the customers are satisfied. Also, salesman will say things are included with furniture that are not. For instance, our sales associate told us that the pillows were included when we purchased our sectional. We find out later that they are not. This I know is not a huge deal, but lying in order to sell something is inexcusable. Our sofa was not delivered as scheduled and was delivered in separate pieces on separate days. That, again is understandable but it would have been nice to hear from the sales associate or customer service to know that they cared. Especially considering my husband had to take time off work to make sure someone was there for the delivery. I understand that some things are beyond the control of the store or the salesperson, but it is common courtesy to contact your customer and make sure they understand. The one star that I do give them is for the quality of the sofa. Other than that, I know we will not return to this store in the future nor recommend that any friends use it.

The Raleigh Store on Glenwood Ave has the worst customer service I have ever experienced. We purchased a set on 11/7 when it arrived the delivery people could not get it in the door. Therefore we had to return to the store to pick a new set. At this time Carlos was helpful. Once the sale was completed it all went downhill from there. We were told delivery would be Dec 11th..no delivery happened..no one called to tell us that it was not happening..Then found out it would be delivered on the 20th by the Cary location. At that time the sales person noticed that the color on chaise was wrong. But positively we were told that the price had lowered on 12/8 so we would get a credit back for the difference which was a 30 day guarantee. Raleigh would process the difference and we should see the credit within in 7 days..that never happened. Then on 12/20 no delivery.. still no one had called from the Raleigh store to apologize or tell us this was going to happen. Then on 12/27 we got our furniture only to find out the chaise was brown..we ordered grey! Customer service said we would get a call from Carlos within 24-48 hours.. hmm no call again! I called and explained our frustrations and Dee said I will assure you we will get this figured out and call you back... this took place on 12/30.. hmm no call yet! We sent an email to corporate.. once again they said that the Raleigh store would credit us and that they would contact us. told to us on 1/2. Hmm no call yet or even an email. However we did find out on 1/2 that our final section of our set would arrive 1/26/19.. no one called us still and why is it acceptable to have to wait for 2 months for your furniture and not have the price honored. Ashley furniture you have ruined our love for your furniture by simply supplying the absolute worst customer service we have ever had! We will not shop here ever again.

The reviews are right, this place is terrible. This has got to be the worst customer service ever. I'm astonished that places with this kind of business model still exist today with the internet and competitive marketplace we have now. This is just like the typical car dealership where you will get badgered and pestered, you cannot know the real prices, you will be pushed with ambiguous discounts, you cannot walk alone in the store without a sales person with you, you will be pressured, you will be lied to. They overinflate the prices so that they can try to manipulate you into thinking you're getting a good deal when they give you these "very special manager" discounts, you can see that their prices online are lower for the same products. The sales people work on commissions so they will upsell as much as they can and will try to make you feel guilty if you don't budge. Their tactics are dirty, dishonest, manipulative, and have no place in today's age, it's incredible to me that people still put up with this kind of shopping. They have a price match guarantee but when you bring them proof of lower price they will be quick to come up with excuse to dismiss it. They will quote you one price but then flip at the checkout charging you more or switching products. When I finally got fed up and tried to cancel my order during the grace period before it was even shipped they were incredibly rude and refused to do so for as long as they could, I had to call them numerous times before they finally did, they would answer my call and when I'd tell them that I want to cancel my order they would put me on hold indefinitely, they would tell me that they will call back and never do, they would give me numerous reasons not to cancel, they were rude, when I kept refusing they would hang up, yes they simply hung up several times. They did have a very nice ashley brand memory foam pillow that I kept :)
